«c5»69...  it could be something nice, but we're talking about months!
69 months! That's the time since the last issue of D.I.S.C, and still
we are not forgotten! Still most sceners remember «c2»D.I.S.C. «c5»with joy,
we are more than pleased. Therefore we come back once again to give YOU
dear reader the best «c2»Digitial Information Service a Computerfreak «c5»can get!«»
«»
During these respective 6 years we have not rested one minute, but done
our best to bring back this «c2»legendary digital magazine. «c5»However, it has
not been easy because of all the «c2»overwhelming problems «c5»we have met. We will
not bore you with all the details... but refer to the article called
«c2»The D.I.S.C. History.«»
«»
«c5»The last years «c2»the scene «c5»has gone through «c2»many changes, «c5»and it has been
a rather hard time for the real amiga enthusiasts. The Amiga has frequently 
gotten new owners, but now finally, the «c2»Amiga Inc. «c5»has ended in the hands
of true amiga lovers and the «c2»future «c5»of the amiga looks much brighter.
Even though the lack of «c2»new hardware «c5»the last 6 years, the sceners have
continued to have «c2»faith «c5»in this fabolous machine and produced lots of
«c5»quality productions.«»
«»
«c5»Last year we got to see quite many high quality productions, such as the
demos «c2»Cybercinematastic, Megademo 2000, I Want To Be Machine, J, Abecedarian,
Arla, Violent Dumb, Back To The Roots, Smurphine - Another O.D,
Neo 2, At The Movies, First Awakening, New Age, Welcome To Our World, Pluss, 
Mayhem, Metatag «c5»and lots of others. We got to see great intros as «c2»Grid2,
Gift, Incision, Ten, Strange Distortion, Tourbus, Omnicrom, Suicidal,
Euskacktro, Modular, Heaven, Electricity, Yoo «c5»and many more. And lots of
mini intros (4k) such as «c2»Humus, Bier, Genoma, Mitosis, Wave, Noisejesus,
Fee, B0rst, Polychrome, Art Of 4k etc. «c5»And a few quality slideshows got
released, like «c2»Divine and Innocence. «c5»In addition to that, we got a few
musicdisks such as Schizofrenia and Despair. Read more about that elsewhere in
«c2»D.I.S.C.«»
«»
«c5»In the diskmag department not that much is happening anymore. 6 years ago
there were lots of quality mags around. Last year we got too see releases
of «c2»Devotion, SeenPoint and Oepir Risti, «c5»and the chartmags «c2»EuroChart and ShowTime. «c5»In
addition to that, some more national mags got out; like «c2»Excess, Beret,
Taboo and Dansktoppen. «c5»The only real regular internationl release was the
EuroChart. We could say the situation has been disasterous the latest
years, and it went worse with the departure of SeenPoint also. However, new
optimism returned with the new plans of D.I.S.C. and the release of
Devotion. But then two days ago it got announced that Devotion was «c2»dead,
«c5»and Magic released his files for Devotion 2. It seems he had gotten into a quarrel with «c2»Darkus. «c5»Anyway,
read more about that «l:articles/bonusreview»elsewhere in D.I.S.C.«le» and in the EuroChart #42. 
Nevertheless, the «c2»optimism «c5»is NOT gone. You're reading a HUGE issue of
D.I.S.C, and Magic has already announced the creation of a «c2»new mag «c5»under
the Nah-Kolor label. And now we're pleased to say that the magscene is better than in a 
long time. «c2»Taboo #3 «c5»got released earlier this year, in addition to the
Devotion 2 files (Party Zone and Magical Moments), the «c2»EuroChart «c5»will be out
the next DAYS, the «c2»ShowTime «c5»staff has
announced they will release their diskmag "soon" also and another issue of
«c2»Trashcan «c5»is under development. In addition to this
there are lots of packmags out there, and also many other packs. We just
have to mention that packs like «c2»Sabotage, Speed, FrozenPack, Zosia, Embrion and
Dreams «c5»are worth to have a look at.«»
«»
As for «c2»D.I.S.C, «c5»we hope to give you the best digital mag there is nowadays!
After months of real hard work, we are pleased to offer you over «c2»1 MB
«c5»of texts, which got to be the biggest scene-related magazine ever. We have
lots of illustrations to go with the various articles to make them «c2»more
interesting. «c5»In addition to the «c2»scene articles, «c5»we also offer a
«c2»«l:articles/gallery»bonus-gallery«le» and a «l:articles/charts»chart.«le» «c5»We have a highly advanced code which makes it
possible to include almost anything in the articles. Therefore we have
hidden many «c2»links «c5»to make it a bit more interesting. As the first mag ever, after
our knowledge, we inserted various modules in the articles. And we also
have links to various other stuff. So just «c2»click «c5»on various words and
you'll never know what happens! ;)  The code will be developed further and
taken to new heights in the next issues, as we have a very active mag
coder.«»
